sd=Fraud Models	This service domain handles the design and maintenance of a portfolio of fraud models used across all production activity to detect potential fraud on the part of customers, merchants and other involved parties	Example of use:A customer fraudulent card use' algorithm is updated to take account of additional transaction utilization data that is available	Analyze history of transactions and fraud cases to discern fraud patterns and develop Rule sets, Decision Trees, and Machine Learning/Predictive models to identify out of pattern transactions or events and their fraud risk score. Support the use of these models and rules in different production contexts and refine the models in response to new and changing patterns
sdpath=fraud-models
crpath=fraud-model-specification
crr=Fraud Model Specification Instance
mcr=Fraud Model Specification
bqs=FunctionalRequirements Testing Production
CONFIG
FraudModelSpecification	create	Create or register an imported fraud model		createFraudModelSpecification		#desc
FraudModelSpecification	execute	Automatically download a fraud model		executeFraudModelSpecification		#desc
FraudModelSpecification	request	Request the use of a fraud model		requestFraudModelSpecification		#desc
FraudModelSpecification	retrieve	Retrieve details about a fraud model		retrieveFraudModelSpecification		#desc
